news.title: Picard Angst India buys land, bungalow in Mumbai for Rs 86.52 crore
news.para: The company has purchased the property from five joint owners, including global banking and finance professional Francis Andrew Rozario, former CEO & executive director at Temasek’s Fullerton Financial Holdings (International).

news.title: Suraksha group to infuse Rs 250 crore, arrange Rs 3,000 crore loan to complete 20,000 Jaypee flats
news.para: ​As per the resolution plan of Suraksha Group submitted in June 2021, Jaypee Infratech Ltd (JIL) will get delisted and public shareholders will be given an aggregate exit at a price of Rs 0.14 crore.

news.title: Irish banks see commercial real estate revaluations as manageable
news.para: A shift to home working has put pressure on the Irish office market, which experienced a boom in recent years thanks largely to high levels of investment from multinational tech firms, some of whom are now cutting back on their hiring sprees, including letting people go.
